    <body>
        <p>Opens the Select Remote for Synchronize dialog, which lets you select the remote you want to use for a pull and push of files. </p>
        <p>After you select the repository, <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> pulls the remote files from the Git repository and merges them with your local database. Then <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> pushes your local changes back to the remote Git repository.</p>
        <p> If necessary, <MadCap:variable name="Other.Product" /> will perform a commit before synchronizing your files.</p>
        <p>You will see this option if your project is bound to Git.</p>
        <p>See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Source_Control/Git/Synchronizing_Files.htm">Synchronizing Source Control Files</MadCap:xref>.</p>
    </body>
